description:
Electricity bills are skyrocketing and water reserves are dwindling, yet Big Tech giants like OpenAI, Meta, and Amazon are thriving. They’ve secured billions in tax breaks while you foot the bill through higher rates and taxes to power their AI servers. ChatGPT's true cost goes far beyond its $20 monthly subscription: consumers are shouldering $9.3 billion in increased electricity costs. Multi-trillion dollar companies are receiving billions in tax breaks, consuming more than 463 million gallons of water during droughts, and signing secret NDAs with city officials. We are subsidizing the very tech billionaires who are actively working to replace human workers.


To support the channel: https://patreon.com/VanessaWingardh

The War of Attrition is developing rapidly and we are trapped between two horns of a dilemma:
1. The cost of automation and production of useful robots is quickly falling.
AND
2. Social safety nets are being deliberately eroded by the Ruling Class.

The writing is on the wall, when Robots become more economical than paying workers for the same labor, workers will lose their jobs and have no social security to fall back on. In “right to work” states companies already need no justification for dismissal of employees. They refuse to raise wages, they fight unemployment 
insurance and they abuse and threaten labor organizers. They seek to deny us the necessary resources to confront them.

The Ruling Class knows what it's doing, they are stalling for time by catching us in the illusion of the Culture War. 
They know that if we mobilize they will lose their monopoly of control on power, wealth and property. 
They are depriving us of the necessary resources we need to resist them.

This is a War of Attrition and right now the working class must engage in a counter-attack. 
The only way out of this catch-22 is to organize  BEFORE the tipping point. 
There is a massive propaganda effort being deployed right now, intended to convince us of our helplessness. 

But it is all lies.

Solidarity, Equality, and Liberty are not just fancy words.

The best time for a General Strike is Now.
